50|$|Both {{examples}} {{have the}} formula L2Mg2, where L represents the bulky anionic bidentate ligand. X-ray crystallographic studies showed an Mg-Mg bond length of 285.1 pm and 284.6 pm. Theoretical studies indicate an essentially ionic formulation Mg22+(L−)2. The Mg22+ ion {{is the group}} 2 analogue of the group 12 Hg22+ (present in e.g. <b>mercury(I)</b> <b>chloride)</b> and Cd22+ ions (present in cadmium(I) tetrachloroaluminate).|$|E
